$interpreted: Diana: ...Are they still taking advantage of the chaos to inflate prices at the port? Hmph... move some people through. If you need to, borrow from the treasury.
Imperial Guard: Understood.
Diana: ...Is there something else?
Imperial Guard: ...Your Majesty, you've been so hard at work ever since the incident with those exploding letters. Maybe you could take a rest?
Diana: Don't worry, the explosion barely scratched me.
Imperial Guard: I'm merely worried about your health, if you keep pushing yourself like this... Also, the terrorist hasn't yet been found.
Imperial Guard: If you wouldn't mind, Your Majesty, I do have a suggestion...
Imperial Guard: While I understand, since the perpetrator hasn't been found, you've been ordered to stay safe in the city...
Imperial Guard: There is an event going on at the Oasis. You could go there, under the auspices of a personal visit?
Diana: Are you saying I should run away?
Imperial Guard: Of course not, Your Majesty! I'm simply concerned about your well-being...
Diana: It's out of the question! The citizens are working hard at rebuilding our homeland! How would it look if I simply ran off and went on vacation!?
Imperial Guard: Your Majesty, I understand you want to show solidarity and pitch in, but... that's all the more reason to take a break every so often!
Imperial Guard: I'm sure if Lazer were here he'd be saying the same thing.
Diana: (Godfather...)
Diana: Very well. That said, I remember a messenger from the Kingdom of the Sun was supposed to be arriving here soon.
Imperial Guard: Don't you worry, I will take care of it.
Jerome: Hmm... So, I should just continue down this way, right?
Jerome: They said there'd be a sandstorm, but I didn't think it would be this big.
Jerome: But I have to get this letter to Diana...
Kittyeyes: Hiya!!
Jerome: Eh? Is someone fighting?
Kittyeyes: Shoulda run while you had the chance!!
Jerome: Uh oh!
Kittyeyes: Who the heck are you?
Jerome: Let's save the introductions for later, they're coming!
Jerome: Wait, I remember you...
Jerome: You're partners with that thief Roger, right? You're... Kittyeyes?
Kittyeyes: And what's it to ya!?
Kittyeyes: There's not a bounty on Roger's head anymore, it was annulled by the queen! Plus, I remember you, too... You were one of those rebel soldiers!
Jerome: Ah... Well, at the time, yeah...
Kittyeyes: ...Anyway... I guess I should still say thank you.
Jerome: Don't mention it.
Nolva: Ah... I fell asleep again...
Nolva: Sorry, Kittyeyes. I just made more trouble for you again...
Kittyeyes: Don't worry about it, Nolva.
Jerome: Ah, she was just asleep?
Nolva: Hmm? Who's this?
Kittyeyes: Let me explain...
Jerome: Ah, so it's void sickness? Isn't that dangerous for her to travel such a long distance?
Nolva: Well, originally I didn't come with Kittyeyes, but Roger ran into some—
Kittyeyes: Nolva!!
Jerome: What?
Kittyeyes: Nothing... Anyway, recently we helped out a merchant, and they gave us two tickets to this Oasis event to thank us.
Kittyeyes: And I figured it'd been a while since I went anywhere with Nolva, so...
Nolva: Huh? But, I remember... umghh...
Jerome: Those tickets look the same as mine.
Kittyeyes: You're going to the Oasis, too?
Jerome: I am, but not for fun. I'm on official business.
Jerome: Why don't we travel together, since we're going to the same place? It might be safer that way.
Kittyeyes: What!? No way!
Jerome: Don't worry, I won't get in your way.
Kittyeyes: That's not why, it's just...
Nolva: Kittyeyes, are you worried because he's a soldier?
Kittyeyes: A little bit... even though Roger and I do have immunity...
Nolva: I understand why you're worried, but... I think Jerome means well. He just wants to escort us.
Kittyeyes: Escort...?
Kittyeyes: He did help us, I guess... It doesn't seem like he has any ill intentions...
Nolva: See! He doesn't look so bad, does he? Seems like an upstanding type of guy!
Kittyeyes: Upstanding, huh? Maybe even a little dopey, to be honest.
Nolva: Kittyeyes!
Kittyeyes: Alright, I get it, Nolva.
Kittyeyes: Alright. Let's head there together, Jerome.
Jerome: Glad to join the team.
Nolva: We're finally out of the sandstorm.
Jerome: Good thing we didn't bump into any more beasts.
Kittyeyes: Hey, I see it!
Nolva: Wow, it's the—
Kittyeyes: Oasis—
Jerome: Sports Day?
Organiser: Hello, are you here for Oasis Sports Day?
Jerome: Yes.
Organiser: Your tickets check out. Welcome aboard! We ask everyone to please change into official Sports Day uniforms.
Jerome: Uniforms? Uh...
Organiser: That's right. Sports Day rules are everyone has to change into Oasis wear.
Organiser: Don't worry, it's included in the ticket. We've prepared everything for you.
Organiser: You even have a pick of the style that suits you best.
Jerome: Yes, but I'm not here to participate...
Kittyeyes: Just follow the rules, Jerome!
Kittyeyes: Come on, Nolva, lets pick out our uniforms.
Nolva: Okay~
Kittyeyes: We want two sexy, beautiful uniforms please.
Nolva: Is something wrong?
Organiser: Ladies, if you don't mind me saying, I don't think that sort of uniform would suit you both.
Kittyeyes: Whaat?
Organiser: Ladies, if I may share my expert opinion, I think that look is better suited for someone a bit older.
Organiser: For example, someone like the lovely woman over there.
Jerome: Queen... Diana?
